@NODE "LibDoGadgetMethodA" "reaction.lib/LibDoGadgetMethodA()"
@{b}

   NAME@{ub}
       LibDoGadgetMethodA -- @{"DoGadgetMethodA" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/DoGadgetMethodA"} for V37 machines
       LibDoGadgetMethod -- Varargs stub for LibDoGadgetMethodA@{b}

   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       result = LibDoGadgetMethodA( Gadget, Window, Requester, Message )
       D0                  A0      A1      A2         A3

       @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} LibDoGadgetMethodA( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *, @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *,
           @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} *, Msg );

       result = LibDoGadgetMethod( Gadget, Window, Requester, MethodID, ...)

       @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52} LibDoGadgetMethod( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *, @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *,
           @{"struct Requester" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 144} *, @{"ULONG" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 52}, ... );@{b}


   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Same as the @{"DoGadgetMethod()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/DoGadgetMethodA"} function of @{"intuition.library" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/MAIN"} V39,
       this function invokes a BOOPSI method and provides context
       information for classes which implement custom Intuition gadgets.

       You should use this function for boopsi gadget objects,
       or for "models" which propagate information to gadgets.

       Unlike @{"DoMethod()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/amiga_lib/DoMethod"}, this function provides a GadgetInfo pointer
       (if possible) when invoking the method.  Some classes may
       require or benefit from this.

       On a V39 machine, this function calls the Intuition function.@{b}

   INPUTS@{ub}
       Gadget = abstract pointer to a boopsi gadget
       Window = window gadget has been added to using @{"AddGList()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/AddGList"} or @{"AddGadget()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/AddGadget"}
       Requester = for REQGADGETs, requester containing the gadget
       Msg = the boopsi message to send@{b}

   RESULT@{ub}
       The object does whatever it wants with the message you sent,
       which might include updating its gadget visuals.

       The return value is defined per-method.@{b}

   NOTES@{ub}
       This function invokes the specified method with a GadgetInfo
       derived from the 'Window' and 'Requester' pointers.  The GadgetInfo
       is passed as the second parameter of the message, except for
       @{"OM_NEW" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 63}, @{"OM_SET" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 65}, @{"OM_NOTIFY" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 69}, and @{"OM_UPDATE" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 70}, where the GadgetInfo
       is passed as the third parameter.

       Implementers of new gadget methods should ensure that the
       GadgetInfo is the second long-word of their message!@{b}

   SEE ALSO@{ub}
       @{"NewObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/NewObject"}, @{"DisposeObject()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/DisposeObject"}, @{"GetAttr()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/GetAttr"}, @{"MakeClass()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/MakeClass"},
       Document "Basic @{"Object" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classusr.h/File" 19}-Oriented Programming @{"System" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/dos/SystemTagList"} for @{"Intuition" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/inline/intuition.h/File" 33}"
       and the "boopsi @{"Class" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/classes.h/File" 36} Reference" document.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "OpenLayoutWindowTagList" "reaction.lib/OpenLayoutWindowTagList()"
@{b}

   NAME@{ub}
       OpenLayoutWindowTagList -- Open a window at a suitable size for layout
       OpenLayoutWindowTags -- Varags stub for OpenLayoutWindowTagList@{b}

   SYNOPSIS@{ub}
       window = OpenLayoutWindowTagList( layout, screen, taglist )

       @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *OpenLayoutWindowTagList( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *,
               @{"struct Screen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 133} *, struct TagList * )

       window = OpenLayoutWindowTags( layout, screen, tag, ... )

       @{"struct Window" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 909} *OpenLayoutWindowTags( @{"struct Gadget" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/intuition.h/File" 214} *,
               @{"struct Screen" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/intuition/screens.h/File" 133} *, Tag, ... )@{b}

   FUNCTION@{ub}
       Determines the minimum size that will fit a layout and opens the window
       at that size. The sizing limits of the window will be set according to
       the layout's limits, and the layout will be added to the window,
       making it relative to window size. The layout will fit the whole inner
       size of the window. It will not be rendered, so you must call
       @{"RefreshGadgets()" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/intuition/RefreshGadgets"}, possibly after adding your border gadgets.

       This function will set InnerWidth, InnerHeight, and the screen for the
       window. Other tags you have to pass yourself.@{b}

   INPUTS@{ub}
       layout -- the layout hierarcy for the window
       screen -- pointer to the screen the window will be opened on
       taglist -- the additional tags for the window.@{b}

   RESULTS@{ub}
       A pointer to the opened window or @{"NULL" LINK "gg:doc/NDK/Guide/Include/exec/types.h/File" 101} if the open failed.

@ENDNODE
